excerpt: Daily-changing menu using local produce at a traditional stone-floored country pub with real ales.
detail_description: The Red Lion is a traditional stone-floored country pub that has won three Isle of Wight Dining Pub of the Year awards and is featured in the Michelin Guide. The cozy and classic chic atmosphere, complete with a fireplace for winter and a beer garden for sunny days, makes it an inviting spot. Visitors can enjoy local produce from the daily-changing menu and even bring their four-legged friends along.
name: The Red Lion
address: Church Pl, Freshwater, PO40 9BP, United Kingdom

detail_description: The Terrace is a charming harbor-side restaurant located in Yarmouth, Isle of Wight, offering stunning views of the waterfront and Yarmouth Castle. The restaurant features two lovely outdoor terraces furnished with Bridgman furniture, as well as glass shelters to ensure a delightful dining experience regardless of the weather. Visitors can enjoy the contemporary dining room adorned with local art and design while savoring the best produce from the Isle of Wight.
name: The Terrace
address: Quay St, Yarmouth, PO41 0PB, United Kingdom

excerpt: Laid-back beachfront restaurant with a terrace serving seafood specialties & grilled meats.
detail_description: "The Hut" is a laid-back beachfront restaurant with a terrace that offers seafood specialties and grilled meats. The restaurant provides a relaxed dining experience with its wide open sun-bleached decking and views of the azure blue sea stretching out over the Solent, reminiscent of dining in the Caribbean. It is open all day during the summer months, allowing guests to enjoy lunch in the sun or candlelit dinner without the need for formal wear.
name: The Hut
address: Colwell Chine Rd, Colwell Bay, Freshwater, PO40 9NP, United Kingdom

excerpt: Quaint pub serving local produce with a menu dependent on what has been caught, foraged or hunted.
detail_description: Nestled in the charming village of Godshill, The Taverners is a delightful pub that embodies the essence of local dining. This quaint establishment prides itself on serving dishes crafted from ingredients that are either caught, foraged, or hunted nearby. With a menu that changes with the seasons, guests can indulge in traditional favorites alongside unique offerings like salt-roasted pig face paired with homemade pork faggot and fresh vegetables sourced from their own garden.
name: The Taverners
address: High St, Godshill, Ventnor PO38 3HZ, United Kingdom

detail_description: Heron is a top-notch Indian restaurant located in Ryde, UK. The establishment has gained recognition as one of the five best Indian restaurants in the area, according to Tripadvisor's updated 2023 rankings. With a diverse menu and an excellent selection of wines, Heron offers exquisite meals at affordable prices. Located on Castle Street, this fine dining experience provides customers with delectable dishes that are specially prepared by the talented team.
name: Heron Ryde
address: 2 Castle St, Ryde, PO33 2EP, United Kingdom

excerpt: Airy, modern eatery offering elevated local British fare & cocktails alongside beach & water views.
detail_description: The Duck is a contemporary, stylish establishment that offers elevated local British cuisine and creative cocktails. It boasts stunning beach and water views, providing a refreshing ambience for diners. Located just a short 5-minute walk from the Easthill Road Bus stop, visitors can conveniently access the restaurant by catching the Southern Vectis No. 8 Bus to St. Helens Causeway using a Day Rider ticket.
name: The Duck
address: Appley Rise, Ryde, PO33 1LE, United Kingdom

excerpt: Guesthouse with airy maritime-themed rooms, a relaxed restaurant and a pub with a patio.
detail_description: The Boathouse is a charming guesthouse located in the quaint village of Seaview, at the eastern end of Ryde. The maritime-themed rooms offer a relaxed and airy atmosphere. The on-site restaurant, run by chefs Joel and Massimo, features a variety of appetizing options made with locally sourced ingredients. Diners can enjoy dishes like prosciutto-wrapped monkfish tail or twelve-hour braised beef in the snug, nautical interior.
name: The Boathouse
address: 2 Springvale Rd, Seaview, PO34 5AW, United Kingdom

excerpt: Airy rooms with free WiFi above a traditional seaside restaurant featuring a waterfront patio.
detail_description: The Crab and Lobster Inn is a charming seaside accommodation with airy rooms offering free WiFi, located above a traditional restaurant with a waterfront patio. Situated in the picturesque town of Bembridge, it's close to the beach and offers easy access to various dining options in the village. The inn is known for its great food, stunning views, and comfortable 4-star accommodations, including family rooms.
name: The Crab and Lobster Inn
address: 32 Forelands Field Rd, Bembridge, PO35 5TR, United Kingdom

excerpt: Home-grown garlic, plus garlic-inspired products and fare in a specialist farm shop with restaurant.
detail_description: The Garlic Farm Shop and Restaurant is a specialist farm shop with a restaurant that offers home-grown garlic and an array of garlic-inspired products. Located near the Sandown-Newport cycle path, it provides an opportunity for visitors to explore the extensive grounds and learn about garlic production. The farm also offers tours of Arreton Valley by foot or tractor, providing a fun day out for families.
name: The Garlic Farm Shop And Restaurant
address: Mersley Ln, Newchurch, Sandown PO36 0NR, United Kingdom

detail_description: Smoking Lobster in Ventnor is a popular dining spot that offers locally sourced produce with a pan-Asian twist. The restaurant prides itself on serving dishes like grilled lobster with miso butter, tender tempura monkfish, and seared scallops. What sets this place apart is its own fishing boat catching seasonal fish right outside the restaurant, ensuring the freshest seafood possible.
name: Smoking Lobster Ventnor
address: Esplanade, Ventnor, PO38 1JT, United Kingdom

excerpt: Grand hotel built in 1832, with elegant rooms, an upscale restaurant and an outdoor pool.
detail_description: The Royal Hotel, a grand establishment dating back to 1832, offers elegant rooms, an upscale restaurant, and an outdoor pool. It is a family-friendly hotel that goes beyond providing just the basics for children. The staff are attentive and accommodating, catering to families with young children by offering pureed meals for babies and warm milk for toddlers. This venerable grande dame on the Isle of Wight exudes an atmosphere reminiscent of a bygone era while still maintaining its vibrancy.
name: The Royal Hotel
address: Belgrave Rd, Ventnor, PO38 1JJ, United Kingdom

detail_description: Thompson's Garden Centre in Newchurch is a delightful place to explore, especially if you have some time to spare before catching a ferry. The on-site cafe offers delectable homemade cakes and scones, with quick service and friendly staff adding to the pleasant experience. It's definitely a worthwhile stop for those looking for quality food and a charming atmosphere.
name: Thompson's Garden Centre - Newchurch
address: Watery Ln, Sandown, PO36 0LX, United Kingdom

excerpt: 18th-century pub with ceiling beams and inglenook fireplace, serving British dishes & fish specials.
detail_description: New Inn is an 18th-century pub known for its charming atmosphere with ceiling beams and an inglenook fireplace. The pub offers a menu of British dishes and fish specials, catering to the traditional meal times that are essential in British culture. Visitors can enjoy fresh fish, crab, and lobster at this award-winning establishment in Shalfleet. The friendly staff and high-quality food make it a popular choice for both locals and visitors alike.
name: New Inn
address: Shalfleet, Newport, PO30 4NS, United Kingdom

excerpt: Comfort food and real ales in a traditional, bare-beamed pub, plus big garden with kids' play area.
detail_description: The Fighting Cocks is a traditional pub located in Godshill, offering comfort food and a selection of real ales. The establishment features a classic atmosphere with bare beams and also boasts a spacious garden complete with a play area for kids. Despite its location between a garden center and car dealership, the pub remains popular among visitors. It has received recognition, placing third in the Best Pub category at the Red Funnel Isle of Wight Awards 2022.
name: The Fighting Cocks
address: Hale Common, Newport, PO30 3AR, United Kingdom

detail_description: Located in Ventnor, The Met offers a taste of the Mediterranean with its seaside patio providing stunning views of the English Channel. The interior is adorned with local artwork on exposed brick walls. Nearby, Ventnor Park offers a relaxing spot for coffee and easy access to the town center and beach. Visitors can enjoy quality tapas and drinks while taking in the beautiful beachfront setting.
name: The Met
address: Esplanade, Ventnor, PO38 1JP, United Kingdom

excerpt: Candlelit tables and British dishes like roast rump of lamb with a port and stilton glaze.
detail_description: Nestled in the quiet streets of Newport, Burrs is a hidden gem known for its delectable British cuisine and intimate candlelit ambiance. Since 1997, this restaurant has prided itself on using locally sourced ingredients to create everything from homemade bread to decadent desserts. The menu offers a variety of European dishes with a modern twist, perfect for romantic dinners or special celebrations.
name: Burrs
address: 27-28 Lugley St, Newport, PO30 5HD, United Kingdom

excerpt: Quirky venue serving locally landed fish in a relaxed ambiance above a lively ground-floor bar.
detail_description: Salty's Pizzeria, Bar & Takeaway is a charming spot located in the yachting town of Yarmouth on the Isle of Wight. The venue offers delicious pizzas made with handcrafted sourdough and locally sourced ingredients. In addition to its mouthwatering pizzas, Salty's also serves as a lively ground-floor bar where guests can enjoy a relaxed ambiance. The attentive and friendly staff provide excellent service, making visitors feel welcome and well taken care of.
name: Salty's Pizzeria, Bar & Takeaway
address: Quay St, Yarmouth, PO41 0PB, United Kingdom

detail_description: The Blacksmith's, located on the outskirts of Carisbrooke, is a beloved eatery on the Isle of Wight. This charming 17th-century pub offers not only a glimpse into history but also delectable cuisine. The atmosphere is always lively and bustling, attracting both locals and visitors alike. Unlike typical establishments that feature arcade games, The Blacksmith's is an adult-oriented pub with a playground for children to enjoy.
name: The Blacksmiths
address: Calbourne Rd, Newport, PO30 5SS, United Kingdom

excerpt: Traditional oak-beamed village pub with garden, serving real ales and classic, locally sourced food.
detail_description: Nestled in the charming village of Newchurch on the Isle of Wight, The Pointer Inn is a delightful traditional pub that exudes warmth and character. With its inviting oak beams and cozy fireplace, it offers a perfect retreat for those seeking comfort after exploring the scenic Bembridge Trail. The pub boasts an expansive beer garden where furry friends can frolic freely in the adjacent field while their owners enjoy refreshing pints of real ale from Fullers.
name: The Pointer Inn
address: High St, Newchurch, Sandown PO36 0NN, United Kingdom

excerpt: Warm rooms and a nautical-themed pub/restaurant in a casual, sea-view inn, plus free breakfast.
detail_description: The Steamer Inn in Shanklin offers warm rooms and a casual, sea-view pub/restaurant with free breakfast. The inn boasts incredible panoramic views across Sandown Bay to the English Channel, making it the perfect spot to enjoy local seafood after a day of exploring or beach activities. The nautical-themed pub serves expertly crafted cocktails made with premium spirits and fresh ingredients. Additionally, guests can enjoy live entertainment at the venue.
name: The Steamer Inn
address: Esplanade, Shanklin, PO37 6BS, United Kingdom
